Following code repo for Creating a Hello World Docker file and then install it.

Excersise Information 
        >Hello World Container
		>Create a Dockerfile that:
		>Uses alpine as the base image.
		>Prints "Hello Docker!" when run.
		>Build the image and run it.

Step 1: Create a Dockerfile

# Use Alpine Linux as the base image
FROM alpine:latest

# Define the command to run when the container starts
CMD ["echo", "Hello Docker!"]

Step 2: Build the Docker image

docker build -t hello-docker .

Step 3: Run the container

docker run hello-docker


Please note this will work on the machine where docker is installed 
